texts.text: >The world is drowning in chaos.
>It persists and spreads unseen to the naked eye,
>but has the power to end relationships and normal life as you know it.
*Growl*
So this is the reason all these demons have been appearing...?
What, this...?
It's time to roll up our sleeves...
And clean them up!
Let's go, four-eyes!
Okay! And would you please stop calling me that...?!
Who cares? You know what to do, right...?

Of course!
Let's go!
>Shiang Sun and Honey's demons leap out,
>and perform a vicious pincer move.
*Shriek*
>Shiang Sun calls to Vince.
Vince! Now!
Already on it!
>Vince's demon has gone and made the demon tumble over.
>Vince then looks to you.
Now!
Finish it!
>Your demon lands a heavy blow to finish them off.
*Scream*

*Snicker*
No mercy.
Our combo went off without a hitch!
We must be...
The strongest team ever!
The best team ever!
Yes, that! You took the words right out of my mouth!
I just followed your lead.
He says that, but he'd never do this with other people.
What's going on?
Shut it. This was the most efficient way to get things done.
Also, don't we need to head back soon to report in?
Yes, we should.

Let's go.
Back to the Hideout!

Hey, y'all!
Back already?
You have to hear this. We pulled off the most incredible combo attack...!
Yeah. We got their boss, so mission accomplished, right?
W-Wait, you didn't do it any justice...!

We're done!
That's that!

Good enough for me!
Nice job, y'all.
Yo, I didn't think you'd wrap things up this quick.
And I hate doin' this to y'all now but...
What is it?

Something else came up.
Yo, check the news.
>The TV is turned to a news program...
We are continuing to receive reports regarding a string of mysterious murders...
Today, another body was discovered in Shinjuku.
Based on the marks and lacerations that were found on each of these bodies,
the working theory at the moment it that these victims were mauled by a large creature of some sort.
No wounds indicating that a weapon was used seem to be present,
and the police believe that a serial killer is behind these murders.
Oh, is that what this is about?
Yo, it's somethin' big that's been doin' this,
and it didn't use any weapons or anythin'.
Hold up. You saying a demon's involved?
Can't say either way.
For now, I'm askin' non-Dx2 members to take a look.
You mean the maid girl and Kazufumi?
Nah, I'm havin' some other folks in our corner take care of it.
Alright.
And they're sayin' that there's evidence that a demon did this.
Damn...
Yo, we're like 90% sure that someone's usin' a demon to do all this.
Nobody would ever think that a demon's the murder weapon.
Ain't that the truth.
Also, you find anythin' good, Chalk Eater?
I did. These victims do seem to have something in common.
There's still a few places I'd like to look, but it'll do for now.
Huh? Where'd a kid like you get all this info?
From the police, of course.
Wait, you mean you hacked them?
Yes. It's my expertise.
And they have no way to trace anything back to me, so there's no need to worry.
Heh. Not bad.
Aight, can you give us a rundown, Chalk Eater?
Yes. Let's start with how every victim seems to be from the "Star of Wisdom" group.

"Star of Wisdom?"
Yo, that giant cult?
They've supposedly been trying to help the weak and impoverished.
However, there's no way to know just how much of that is true.
Their catchphrase claims that, "Reality is here,"
but there are also reports of people joining after running from their own homes.
Everything about them seems shady.
Yo, I've heard of them too. They've got young and old people from all over linin' up to join.

Huh, really?
Are they that popular?
Honey wants to know their secret.
Yo, hold up. You might get brainwashed and stuff, you know?
I just posted a video warnin' people about them too.
The police seem to have undercovers investigating as well,
but they seem to be having trouble finding a smoking gun.
And they never will if a demon's the one behind all this.
Light bulb! So is this what you're thinking, Megakin?
This cult is using a demon to kill all these people.
That's right.
No, we can't say for sure. We ain't got any proof.
But I need y'all to look into this.
That includes the "Star of Wisdom" group as a whole.
Seriously?! You're making us jump back in the fire?
Yo, Carbon Black...
I didn't say anyone will do.
Huh?
I found countless photos of victims in the police's servers...
Some remained mostly whole, but some were missing the upper halves of their bodies.
To be fair, that's a worst case scenario.
But there's no telling you'll run into this thing.
So you're saying not all of us will be able to handle what happens?
You're saying that I can...
It's me or a certain other deviant, eh?
And they're not here, conveniently.
Honey want to go. Honey's a Homunculus after all!
Blood, gore and dead bodies don't bother me at all.
I do feel bad for them sometimes but...
You're not just a Homunculus, Honey. You have a soul.
Sadly, I'm not sure I can handle something like this...
But I thought you liked that kind of stuff, four-eyes?

*Sigh*
You seem to be misunderstanding.
I'm not secretly a crazed murderer or anything.
Movies as pure fiction. It's still a crime to do that to actual people.
I see. So as long as it's fake...
You could phrase it better, but yes.
But you can count on my help.
Something about this cult feels wrong and it's bugging me.
Honey wants to know too. I don't understand why people need religion.
I want to know more about what makes people tick.
Fine. If she's going, I'm going too.
You owe me some damn good coffee when we get back.
Aight, you got it.
Yo, I'm stayin' to help get more intel. How about you, Newbie?
I'm good to go!
Do I have a choice?
Yay! Let's go!
Heh. We're in the same boat,

Aight, y'all.
We're countin' on you.
